			<div class="content" id="post-content-4764305">
									

<p>Hello! I'm Stephen. I found SCP via someone that mentioned undoubtly the most well-known SCP of all, SCP-173. I think it was referenced in a Reddit comment and I thought I stumbled upon some really shadey, top secret stuff! From there I found my way around the site and read a lot of the top-rated stuff. I would soon realise that DJKaktus is extremely good at what they do.</p>
<p>I'm unsure what I want to do on the site yet besides reading and rating. Of course I'd love to create an SCP page one day but I'll be sure to study the &quot;How to Write an SCP&quot; page for a while first. I'm an immeasurable amount of talent away from creating something like the SCP-4205 page. I was so impressed by how it was done!</p>
<p>For this month's random question: I'd probably say no. My current favourite SCP is 507, and as funny it would be, I'd probably lose him after the first shift. Especially being a miniature version!</p>
<p>Anyway, back to reading some more SCPs. Ciao for now!</p>

