			<div class="content" id="post-content-4767720">
									

<p>Hi everyone, I'm Nathan, but my online tag is usually some combination of Invictus/Rage(d), which is a combination of poem names.</p>
<p>I've been reading SCP for probably a decade, but only finally during quarantine have I become more interested in contribution. I am a philosophy professor, so more abstract and complex SCPs appeal to me; my favorite SCP is 093, which is the first SCP I read that really got me from a horror perspective.</p>
<p>The thing that specifically made me sign up now is not just quarantine, but the most recent contest posting, which compelled me from several perspectives. I don't actually think I want to join a team, but maybe I do? but I am regardless kinda compelled by the structure, and now have been working my way through the canons that are going to be revisited. I definitely want to give feedback on both concepts and writing, and maybe end up writing my own.</p>
<p>I also really want to just chat with other people who like SCPs. A miniature 093 strikes me as somewhere between horrifying and useless; does it open portals into miniature worlds? If so, I don't wanna think about the implications. If it just opens tiny portals, that seems useless.</p>

